insurance_t1_data <- insurance_data %>%
  mutate(insurance = fct_recode(insurance, " " = "no", " " = "yes")) %>% 
    mutate(
    education = fct_relevel(
      education,
      "none", "ged", "highschool", "bachelor", "master", "phd", "other"
    )
  ) %>% 
  mutate(
    education = fct_recode(
      education,
      " " = "none",
      " (GED)" = "ged",
      " " = "highschool",
      "" = "bachelor",
      "" = "master",
      "  (PhD)" = "phd",
      "" = "other"
    )
  ) %>% 
  mutate(
    region = fct_recode(region,
      " " = "midwest",
      "-" = "northeast",
      "" = "south",
      "" = "west"
    ),
    ethnicity = fct_recode(ethnicity,
      "" = "afam",
      "" = "cauc",
      "" = "other"
    ),
    gender = fct_recode(gender,
      "" = "male",
      "" = "female"
    )
  )

# ggplot2 . .

plot_categorical <- function(df) {
  categorical_vars <- names(df)[sapply(df, function(x) is.factor(x) | is.character(x))]
  
  plots <- list()
  for(var in categorical_vars) {
    freq_data <- as.data.frame(table(df[[var]]))
    names(freq_data) <- c("Category", "Count")
    freq_data$Percentage <- round(freq_data$Count / sum(freq_data$Count) * 100, 1)
    freq_data$Label <- paste0(freq_data$Count, "\n", freq_data$Percentage, "%")
    
    freq_data <- freq_data[order(-freq_data$Count), ]
    freq_data$Category <- factor(freq_data$Category, levels = freq_data$Category)
    
    p <- ggplot(freq_data, aes(x = Category, y = Count, fill = Category)) +
      geom_bar(stat = "identity", alpha = 0.8) +
      
      geom_text_repel(
        aes(label = Label),
        color = "black",
        size = 3.5,
        fontface = "bold",
        direction = "y",
        nudge_y = max(freq_data$Count) * 0.05, 
        segment.color = "gray50",
        segment.size = 0.3,
        min.segment.length = 0.1,
        box.padding = 0.2,
        point.padding = 0.2,
        lineheight = 0.8
      )  +
      
      scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set2") +
      labs(title = paste(":", var),
           subtitle = paste(":", nrow(freq_data)),
           x = "", y = "") +
      theme_minimal() +
      theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1),
            legend.position = "none",
            plot.title = element_text(face = "bold", size = 14)) +
      scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.15))) 
    
    plots[[var]] <- p
  }
  
  grid.arrange(grobs = plots, ncol = 3)
}

plot_numeric<- function(df) {
  numeric_vars <- names(df)
  
  plots <- list()
  for(var in numeric_vars) {
    mean_val <- mean(df[[var]], na.rm = TRUE)
    median_val <- median(df[[var]], na.rm = TRUE)
    sd_val <- sd(df[[var]], na.rm = TRUE)
    
    p <- ggplot(df, aes(x = .data[[var]])) +
      geom_histogram(aes(y = after_stat(density)),
                     bins = 25,
                     fill = "lightblue",
                     alpha = 0.7,
                     color = "white",
                     linewidth = 0.3) +

      geom_density(color = "darkgreen",
                   linewidth = 1.2,
                   alpha = 0.8) +
      geom_vline(xintercept = median_val,
                 color = "red",
                 linewidth = 1.2,
                 linetype = "dashed") +
      
      annotate("label",
               x = Inf, y = Inf,
               label = paste0(": ", round(mean_val, 2), "\n",
                             ": ", round(median_val, 2), "\n", 
                             "SD: ", round(sd_val, 2)),
               hjust = 1.1, vjust = 1.5,
               size = 3.5,
               color = "black",
               fontface = "bold") +
      labs(title = paste(":", var),
           x = var,
           y = "") +
      theme_minimal() +
      theme(
        plot.title = element_text(face = "bold", size = 14, hjust = 0.5),
        panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.major = element_line(color = "gray90", linewidth = 0.3),
        plot.background = element_rect(fill = "white", color = NA)
      )
    
    plots[[var]] <- p
  }
  
  wrap_plots(plots, ncol = 2) +
    plot_annotation(
      title = "  ",
      theme = theme(plot.title = element_text(size = 16, face = "bold", hjust = 0.5))
    )
}

calculate_rr_universal <- function(data, exposure_var, outcome_var = "insurance") {

  tab <- data %>% 
    select(all_of(c(exposure_var, outcome_var))) %>% 
    table()
  
  levels <- rownames(tab)
  results <- data.frame()

  if(length(levels) == 2) {
    rr_result <- riskratio(tab, rev = "columns")

    results <- as.data.frame(rr_result$measure) %>%
      mutate(
        variable = exposure_var,
        level = rownames(.),
        comparison = paste(levels[1], "vs", levels[2]),
        reference = levels[1],
        .before = 1
      ) %>%
      rename(
        rr = estimate,
        rr_lower = lower,
        rr_upper = upper
      )
    
  } else {

    for(i in 1:(length(levels)-1)) {
      for(j in (i+1):length(levels)) {
        pair_tab <- tab[c(i, j), ]
        rr_result <- riskratio(pair_tab, rev = "columns")
        
        pair_results <- as.data.frame(rr_result$measure) %>%
          mutate(
            variable = exposure_var,
            level = rownames(.),
            comparison = paste(levels[i], "vs", levels[j]),
            reference = levels[i],
            .before = 1
          ) %>%
          rename(
            rr = estimate,
            rr_lower = lower,
            rr_upper = upper
          )
        
        results <- rbind(results, pair_results)
      }
    }
  }
  
  return(results)
}

rr_results <- data.frame()

for(var in categorical_vars) {
  var_results <- calculate_rr_universal(insurance_data, var)
  rr_results <- rbind(rr_results, var_results)
}


rr_clean <- rr_results %>%  filter(!is.na(rr_lower)) %>% 
  arrange(variable, rr)

ggplot(rr_clean, aes(x = rr, y = reorder(comparison, rr))) +
  geom_point(size = 3, alpha = 0.8) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(xmin = rr_lower, xmax = rr_upper), 
                 width = 0.2, alpha = 0.6, orientation='y') +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 1, linetype = "dashed", color = "red") +
  facet_wrap(~ variable, scales = "free_y", ncol = 2) +
  labs(title = "  ( vs  )",
       x = "Relative Risk (RR)  95% ",
       y = "") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.y = element_text(size = 12))
